==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enginery
<hw>En"gine*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
or art of managing engines, or artillery.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Engines, in general; instruments of war.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Training his devilish <qex>enginery</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Any device or contrivance; machinery; structure or
arrangement.</def> <rj><au>Shenstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Engine-sized</ent>⟦br⟧
